Surface 73 F.  Drought continues - lake at its low point in range.
Turnover occurring.  Loons gone.  Recorded 7/8" rain.  60% of lake covered with chara algae.
Major algae bloom occurred.  Water turned yellow/brown.
Surface temp hit 90 F on Memorial Day.  Algae bloom exploded and never went away.
Water temp 76 F- loon chicks present and well
Common terns sighted.  Loons seemed to be on own.
Surface temp 69.8 F.  Canada geese reappearing on lake.  Weed die off occurring.  Nights cooling down.
Fall colors near peak.  5 geese around island.  10 mallards on lake - weeds are dying off.
Water 62 degrees F Water 62 degrees F
Water 72 degrees F.  Visability from algae a problem.
